				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Stop the cry and whine<a name="65927"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Oct 7 04 12:03 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Seriously, some people need to stop whine and cry all the time. Lull got fixed and didn't last 5 mins, some people cried like it's the end of the world. AE kite nerfed, some people cried like it's the end of the world and threatened to quit EQ (or did actually quit, but not like I care...) . /melody was put on test, some people cried like it's the end of the world.
<br />

<br />
I used lull and still using lull. I AE kited and still using AE song during raid for slowing plow mobs etc. I used to twist with song gems, I am twisting with /stop /cast #, and I will be using /melody if it goes live and if I see fit. I take whatever the game designers throw at me and work with/around changes/features/fixes/nerfs.
<br />

<br />
A lot of fixes, nerfs, changes are design decisions mostly. There are no rules to determine if a class, or a skill in a game is too powerful and needs to be nerfed. There are no formulas to calculate what UI/game mechanism is good and what is bad. As I am aware, there are no existing state or federal law that prohibits game designers from changing a feature if it has been in the system for X number of years. There is no policy in the BBB states designers must response to each comment/suggestion/compliant/rant from each indiviual gamers and make the changes within X number of days.
<br />

<br />
Yeah, it's good business pratice and it's for the company's best interest to keep us, customers, happy. And I believe whatever they try to do to the game is to keep us, as a collectly 500,000 or whatever number of people happy, not just the 1,200 or whatever group of people of class X using ability Y.
<br />

<br />
Everyone uses the term &quot;game balance&quot; all the time but a lot of players seem to forget what game balance really means.
<br />

<br />
There is nothing wrong with discussing game issues and maybe go on a little debate about stuff and voice our opinions, it's constructive and fun and all. Things are very likely to get changed the based on the player base (player base as a whole, not just certain small interest groups, as a whole) opinions. But some people have got to drop the &quot;this world evoles around me and I'll cry and whine and threaten to quit EQ if things don't go my way&quot; mentality.
<br />

<br />
That's my long winded way of saying, some people need to stop bitching so much about EQ.</span></td>
