Even if you go to a local racing track (not talking about illegal street racing), you pay a fee to run a solo timed lap and the organizer compare all the competitors' lap times and determine a winner. They have regulations on what modifications on the car are allowed.
<br />

<br />
So yeah, you own the car, you pay the fees to enter the race, but you still have to follow their rules or you don't paticipate in that race.
